<p>The final command above adds the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/ws" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">WebSocket</a> and <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/redis" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Redis</a> dependencies to your project. You are now ready to write some code!</p>



<p><strong>Writing the WebSocket server</strong></p>



<p>Open your favorite code editor for Node.js (I use <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Visual Studio Code</a>) and simply enter the code <mark>“code .”</mark>&nbsp;to open the current directory. In your editor, create a new file called <mark>server.js</mark>.</p>



